text: Mr. Naughton, you may proceed whenever you’re ready.
Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.
Is there anything in this record that would indicate the members would not be free to go out and engage their own counsel of their own selection?
No, there is not Your Honor.
Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the members of this Court.
What’s the name of the Virginia case?
The name of the Virginia case is exactly the same as the Brotherhood, namely, State Bar of Virginia versus the Brotherhood.
I’m talking about the one you were talking about?
Well --
You said this was a kind of a duplicate of it?
Yes.
I just want its name in --
Alright.
Page what?
It is 207 Virginia, page 182, also, 149 S.E.2d 265.
May it please the Court.
Would you mind Mr. Naughton, you did not cross petition when the Virginia State Bar brought its petition here, did you?
That’s correct, Your Honor.
And you did not seek the cert here when leave was denied to appeal from the final decree finally entered in the Richmond Chancery Court?
That's correct also, Your Honor.
